ke anywhere.<\/li><li><strong>Hat <\/strong>&#x2013; Always take a hat\/cap to protect you against that beautiful Colombian sunshine<\/li><li><strong>Long socks &amp; trousers<\/strong> &#x2013; You might also want to take long socks &amp; trousers for some hikes, night walks, or evenings outside to cover your legs and prevent mosquito bites.<\/li><li><strong>Suitable footwear<\/strong> &#x2013; Good walking shoes\/sneakers\/sandals are a must. Hikes can be somewhat challenging with muddy or rocky paths. It&#x2019;s not wise to wear flip-flops here.&#xA0;<\/li><li><strong>Earplugs<\/strong> &#x2013; Your nights can be disturbed by animal sounds, music, or the sound of the waves when sleeping in your hammock\/tent in Colombia. Earplugs save you from having a sleepless night!&#xA0;<\/li><li><strong>Camera<\/strong> &#x2013; Capture memories of your 3 weeks in Colombia with a waterproof camera like a GoPro, or get good protection gear for your camera so you won&#x2019;t have problems if it rains unexpectedly.&#xA0;<\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/go\/anker-powerbank\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>Power bank<\/strong><\/a> &#x2013; For long hikes, power outages, or moments in the jungle, it&#x2019;s helpful to have a power bank to recharge your phone (<a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/go\/anker-powerbank\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">get one here<\/a>).<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/22143059\/minca-colombia-23.jpg\" alt=\"things to do minca colombia hiking\"><\/noscript><img width=\"261\" height=\"338\" alt=\"things to do minca colombia hiking\" class=\"wp-image-88414 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1484px) 100vw, 1484px\" data-